   1         0                            ;
   2         0                            ;   branches.asm -- every Type 11 Bcc and BR (Type 25)
   3         0                            ;
   4         0                            ;   Adds coverage for BE, BNE, BC, BNC, BP, BN, BV, BNV, BGT, BLT,
   5         0                            ;   BH, BNH.  (BGE and BLE are already covered by bubble.asm.)
   6         0                            ;   BR is also exercised here with a bare-label operand, which the
   7         0                            ;   port fixed by routing Type 25's Dir/Rel path through Type 11
   8         0                            ;   (the same Bcc encoder the conditional variants use) — the 1990
   9         0                            ;   code had it going to Type 15 (JMP) which required an Absolute
  10         0                            ;   operand type, so "BR Label" was broken.
  11         0                            ;
  12         0                            ;   Each branch targets the next label, producing a tiny chain of
  13         0                            ;   branches each 2 bytes apart.  We don't care whether each condition
  14         0                            ;   is actually taken at runtime — the test is that the assembler
  15         0                            ;   accepts every mnemonic with a bare-label (Direct) operand.
  16         0                            ;
